\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"IJF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the matter\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1656}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Following the Olympic Games, a full review and investigation of the situation will be conducted and further action will be taken if needed,\\\" the IJF said in the statement.\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1805, \"end\": 1808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"IJF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"a full review\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"investigation\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1737}, {\"ngram\": \"further action\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1774}, {\"ngram\": \"the statement\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The IJF firmly upholds the principles of fair play, the Olympic spirit, and non-discrimination.\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1837, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"IJF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Judo_Federation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the principles\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1870}, {\"ngram\": \"fair play\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1883}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic spirit\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1903}, {\"ngram\": \"discrimination\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1927}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We believe that sport should remain a realm of integrity and fairness, free from the influences of international conflicts.\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 2052, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1950}, {\"ngram\": \"a realm\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"integrity\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1985}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 1998}, {\"ngram\": \"the influences\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2024}, {\"ngram\": \"international conflicts\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, athletes often become victims of broader political disputes which are against the values of sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2076}, {\"ngram\": \"victims\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2097}, {\"ngram\": \"broader political disputes\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2127}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2156}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2165}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday, Butbul showed up for his scheduled bout against Dris at the Champs de Mars Arena, stepped on the mat, and did the customary dojo bowing to where his opponent should have been standing, before leaving to prepare for another match.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2409, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2178}, {\"ngram\": \"Butbul\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2186}, {\"ngram\": \"his scheduled bout\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2219}, {\"ngram\": \"Dris\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"the Champs de Mars Arena\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2260}, {\"ngram\": \"the mat\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2280}, {\"ngram\": \"the customary dojo\", \"from\": 2290, \"to\": 2308}, {\"ngram\": \"his opponent\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2337}, {\"ngram\": \"another match\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2408}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also on Sunday, Tajikistani judoka Nurali Emomali, 22, refused to shake hands with his Israeli counterpart Baruch Shmailov, 29, in round 16 of the men's under 66 kg competition judo competition at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2498, \"end\": 2505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.8698839244905917, \"rank\": 0.14957821600204665, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baruch_ben_Neriah\", \"score\": 0.999777273339421, \"rank\": 0.0001931240318332602, \"text\": \"Baruch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baruch_ben_Neriah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baruch_ben_Neriah\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2425}, {\"ngram\": \"hands\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"round\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2547}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2561}, {\"ngram\": \"66 kg\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"competition judo competition\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2604}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2626}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emomali won the match and instead of shaking hands with Shmailov, which is customary to do at the end of a bout, he walked off the mat saying \\\"Allah Akbar,\\\" which is Arabic for \\\"God is great.\\\"\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Emomali\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2635}, {\"ngram\": \"the match\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"hands\", \"from\": 2673, \"to\": 2678}, {\"ngram\": \"Shmailov\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2729}, {\"ngram\": \"a bout\", \"from\": 2